      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-[#4F3E29]">
        <p>
          The problem? Good equipment is expensive. A single reach truck can cost RM80,000-200,000. If you pay cash, you drain your working capital. If you don't upgrade, you fall behind.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's where <strong>warehouse equipment financing</strong> comes in. Let's talk about how you can get the tools you need with <strong>0% down payment</strong> options.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-[#8B6F47] mt-8 mb-4">Why Financing Beats Cash for Warehousing</h2>
        
        <p>
          Most Malaysian warehouse owners we talk to are busy people. They're juggling transport schedules, staff, and customer demands. When they need a new forklift, their first instinct might be to just pay cash and get it over with.
        </p>
        
        <p>But here's why the "Uncle in Finance" (that's us) recommends financing instead:</p>
        
        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Preserve Your Cash Flow:</strong> In logistics, cash is king. You need it for diesel, maintenance, and unexpected opportunities. Financing lets you keep that cash while paying for the equipment as it generates revenue.</li>
          <li><strong>Tax Benefits:</strong> Did you know that hire purchase and leasing often come with tax advantages? You can typically claim capital allowances or deduct lease payments as business expenses. (Check with your tax agent for the exact details!)</li>
          <li><strong>Upgrade Faster:</strong> Don't wait three years to save up for that automated sorter. Get it now, increase your efficiency today, and pay for it over time.</li>
          <li><strong>Beat Inflation:</strong> The price of machinery rarely goes down. By locking in a financing deal now, you're essentially "buying" today's prices with tomorrow's Ringgit.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-[#8B6F47] mt-8 mb-4">What Kind of Warehouse Equipment Can You Finance?</h2>
        
        <p>If it helps your warehouse run better, we can probably help you finance it. Common items include:</p>
        
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Material Handling Equipment:</strong> Forklifts (diesel, electric, LPG), reach trucks, pallet jacks, and order pickers.</li>
          <li><strong>Storage Systems:</strong> High-density racking, mezzanine floors, and automated storage and retrieval systems (ASRS).</li>
          <li><strong>Packaging Machinery:</strong> Automatic wrapping machines, conveyors, and labeling systems.</li>
          <li><strong>Loading Dock Equipment:</strong> Dock levelers, industrial doors, and heavy-duty ramps.</li>
        </ul>

